description: Number of partitions of n into parts 6k+2 or 6k+3.
formula: Euler transform of period 6 sequence [ 0, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, ...]. - _Michael Somos_, Feb 09 2012G.f.: 1 / (Product_{k>0} (1 - x^(6*k - 4)) * (1 - x^(6*k - 3))). - _Michael Somos_, Feb 09 2012a(n) ~ exp(Pi*sqrt(2*n)/3) * Gamma(1/3) / (4 * 2^(1/3) * sqrt(3) * Pi^(2/3) * n^(2/3)). - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Aug 27 2015
mathematica: nmax = 100; CoefficientList[Series[Product[1/((1 - x^(6k+2))*(1 - x^(6k+3))), {k, 0, nmax}], {x, 0, nmax}], x] (* _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Aug 27 2015 *)
